Sophie’s spastic diplegia means she cannot stand and instead shuffles around on her knees. She is only able to take a few steps with the aid of a frame and cannot play outside with her friends.

Her family, from Dukinfield, Greater Manchester, bought the £1,200 bicycle using some of the donations after her physiotherapist recommended it to prepare her for surgery.

Sophie’s mother, former nurse Allison, 40, said it was ‘life changing’.

She said: ‘Just using it means Sophie’s doing things and seeing things she’s not seen before because she’s always been strapped up in a wheelchair.

‘It has given her the opportunity to use her legs and so much more independence.

