‘She can go out with other children now when they’re playing in the street, instead of having to sit in her chair waving at them.’

Mrs Thomlinson said she and husband Craig, 44, would have had to save ‘for a long time’ to buy the bicycle without the donations.

‘Being able to give Sophie this bit of independence has entirely been down to the generosity of Daily Mail readers,’ she added. ‘They have given her wheels and started her on a journey where hopefully the next step will be walking.’

Sophie’s brother Lewis, 14, said: ‘I’m just glad my sister can go out on her bike with me now. We are going to go to the park together.’

