An anonymous donor has already pledged free flights for the family to travel to St Louis Children’s Hospital in Missouri when they get the go-ahead from Dr Tae Park, the American surgeon who pioneered the procedure.

Funds permitting, Sophie could have the operation next year when she is three. With intensive physiotherapy, she could be walking by five.

The Thomlinsons are raising money through the charity Tree of Hope and any excess will go towards helping other disabled children.

